1
00:00:05,715 --> 00:00:08,248
♪

2
00:01:06,759 --> 00:01:09,059
[JEWELRY JINGLING]

3
00:01:13,499 --> 00:01:14,977
That's every Senate press release

4
00:01:15,001 --> 00:01:16,001
for the last month.

5
00:01:17,503 --> 00:01:20,637
Thanks. Anyone ever tell you you're a noisy one?

6
00:01:22,808 --> 00:01:23,785
I like metal.

7
00:01:23,809 --> 00:01:25,237
[GIGGLES]

8
00:01:25,261 --> 00:01:27,156
How lovely for you.

9
00:01:27,180 --> 00:01:28,723
Now, lose 'em, I can't think.

10
00:01:28,747 --> 00:01:32,499
Then have a seat, and I'll teach you the angry phone voice.

11
00:01:34,437 --> 00:01:36,765
The new intern's something, huh?

12
00:01:36,789 --> 00:01:39,268
Who, Tina? Nah, too cool for me.

13
00:01:39,292 --> 00:01:40,302
Excuse me?

14
00:01:40,326 --> 00:01:42,254
Well, look at her. She's gorgeous.

15
00:01:42,278 --> 00:01:45,440
She gets to hang out with the famous Lois Lane all day.

16
00:01:45,464 --> 00:01:47,092
Me? I'm just a nobody.

17
00:01:47,116 --> 00:01:49,261
You're selling yourself short.

18
00:01:49,285 --> 00:01:50,262
Ask her out.

19
00:01:50,286 --> 00:01:51,963
I already tried, twice.

20
00:01:51,987 --> 00:01:53,948
First time, she said her cat was sick.

21
00:01:53,972 --> 00:01:54,933
And the second?

22
00:01:54,957 --> 00:01:56,902
She told me to buzz off.

23
00:01:56,926 --> 00:01:59,254
She's learning from Lois already.

24
00:01:59,278 --> 00:02:00,278
Jimmy, wait.

25
00:02:02,465 --> 00:02:04,443
<i>[SIRENS WAILING, HELICOPTER WHIRRING]</i>

26
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:05,610
Look at that, another one.

27
00:02:05,634 --> 00:02:06,694
It's every week now.

28
00:02:06,718 --> 00:02:08,046
What is it with these people?

29
00:02:08,070 --> 00:02:09,948
Don't know. Never seen anything like it.

30
00:02:09,972 --> 00:02:10,982
Second one this week.

31
00:02:11,006 --> 00:02:12,951
[GROUP CHATTERING]

32
00:02:12,975 --> 00:02:14,453
[SIREN WAILING]

33
00:02:14,477 --> 00:02:16,721
REPORTER: <i>What started as a minor moving violation</i>

34
00:02:16,745 --> 00:02:18,623
<i>has turned into the latest perilous pursuit</i>

35
00:02:18,647 --> 00:02:19,980
<i>through downtown Metropolis.</i>

36
00:02:21,534 --> 00:02:24,096
The suspect has just veered onto Southend Highway

37
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,047
and is headed right toward Humphrey Plaza.

38
00:02:26,071 --> 00:02:27,516
Humphrey Plaza?

39
00:02:27,540 --> 00:02:28,933
That's right outside.

40
00:02:28,957 --> 00:02:31,353
WOMAN: Wait, hey, let's go over there.

41
00:02:31,377 --> 00:02:34,356
[GROUP CHATTERING]

42
00:02:34,380 --> 00:02:38,015
♪

43
00:02:50,263 --> 00:02:52,807
[TIRES SCREECH]

44
00:02:52,831 --> 00:02:54,732
[SIRENS WAILING]

45
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:05,959
Whoa!

46
00:03:12,501 --> 00:03:14,368
Get lower, I want a better shot!

47
00:03:23,095 --> 00:03:26,146
[CROWD SCREAMING]

48
00:03:33,973 --> 00:03:36,785
WOMAN: Look at that! It's Superman!

49
00:03:36,809 --> 00:03:38,119
[CROWD CHATTERING]

50
00:03:38,143 --> 00:03:40,088
WOMAN 2: He saved everybody, it was amazing!

51
00:03:40,112 --> 00:03:41,456
Get the crew out.

52
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,946
Gimme a hand!

53
00:03:48,321 --> 00:03:51,271
Ah! Ooh!

54
00:03:54,393 --> 00:03:55,393
Ah.

55
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:04,051
Come on, wake up.

56
00:04:05,838 --> 00:04:07,399
[COUGHING]

57
00:04:07,423 --> 00:04:08,901
How's he doing?

58
00:04:08,925 --> 00:04:10,101
I think he's all right.

59
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:12,053
Paramedics are on their way.

60
00:04:12,077 --> 00:04:13,921
Got time for a statement, Superman?

61
00:04:13,945 --> 00:04:14,945
You wouldn't want it.

62
00:04:15,932 --> 00:04:18,014
Thanks for your help, Jimmy.

63
00:04:19,602 --> 00:04:22,097
Cut. Hey, Olsen, you're friends with Superman, right?

64
00:04:22,121 --> 00:04:23,165
Want to do an interview?

65
00:04:23,189 --> 00:04:24,266
Uh, I don't think

66
00:04:24,290 --> 00:04:26,835
I'd be real comfortable with that.

67
00:04:26,859 --> 00:04:28,503
Why not? Camera-shy?

68
00:04:28,527 --> 00:04:31,673
No, but it's not like I'd call us "pals" or anything.

69
00:04:31,697 --> 00:04:33,425
Well, you know him, right?

70
00:04:33,449 --> 00:04:34,926
Yeah.

71
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:37,562
That's good enough for me.

72
00:04:37,586 --> 00:04:40,232
<i>So how would you characterize your friendship with Superman?</i>

73
00:04:40,256 --> 00:04:42,234
<i>Real comfortable. I'd call us pals.</i>

74
00:04:42,258 --> 00:04:44,852
There you have it. Superman has a pal.

75
00:04:44,876 --> 00:04:47,122
My investigative team has uncovered link after link

76
00:04:47,146 --> 00:04:48,723
between the Man of Steel

77
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:51,410
and James Olsen Junior, "Jimmy" to his friends.

78
00:04:51,434 --> 00:04:52,928
According to our research,

79
00:04:52,952 --> 00:04:55,380
you single-handedly saved Superman's skin

80
00:04:55,404 --> 00:04:57,348
from both the Parasite and Luminus.

81
00:04:57,372 --> 00:05:00,369
Plus, we're told you went undercover at his request

82
00:05:00,393 --> 00:05:03,004
to crack Intergang's connection to Apokolips.

83
00:05:03,028 --> 00:05:05,340
Is all of this true? Yeah.

84
00:05:05,364 --> 00:05:07,426
LOIS: What? Hold it right there.

85
00:05:07,450 --> 00:05:10,027
First of all, Superman saved us from Luminus,

86
00:05:10,051 --> 00:05:11,096
not the other way around.

87
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:13,731
And second, what am I, chopped liver?

88
00:05:13,755 --> 00:05:16,473
Aw, I'm sure Superman likes you too.

89
00:05:19,996 --> 00:05:20,973
[SIGHS]

90
00:05:20,997 --> 00:05:22,029
TINA: Jimmy?

91
00:05:23,082 --> 00:05:25,594
Okay, lay it on. I deserve it.

92
00:05:25,618 --> 00:05:26,711
I was wondering

93
00:05:26,735 --> 00:05:29,381
if you still wanted to go out with me sometime.

94
00:05:29,405 --> 00:05:30,899
I-I'm sorry, what?

95
00:05:30,923 --> 00:05:34,152
I'll take that as a yes. Tonight okay?

96
00:05:34,176 --> 00:05:37,155
I'll see you right after work.

97
00:05:37,179 --> 00:05:39,240
Uh, yeah. Okay.

98
00:05:39,264 --> 00:05:42,410
Heh-heh-hey. Superman's pal, right?

99
00:05:42,434 --> 00:05:43,461
Breakfast, on the house.

100
00:05:43,485 --> 00:05:45,080
Huh?

101
00:05:45,104 --> 00:05:46,415
Superman's pal?

102
00:05:46,439 --> 00:05:47,666
From TV, last night?

103
00:05:47,690 --> 00:05:49,734
WOMAN: Oh, can I have your autograph?

104
00:05:49,758 --> 00:05:50,907
[GROUP CHATTERING]

105
00:05:52,778 --> 00:05:54,672
Oh, glad you liked your dinner, Jimbo.

106
00:05:54,696 --> 00:05:57,625
But next time, come by with your buddy, Superman.

107
00:05:57,649 --> 00:06:00,178
You bet. Thanks again for picking up the tab.

108
00:06:00,202 --> 00:06:01,629
My subway's that way.

109
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:04,349
Oh, oh, okay. Now, where was I?

110
00:06:04,373 --> 00:06:07,118
Oh, yeah, the Fortress of Solitude.

111
00:06:07,142 --> 00:06:08,186
You've been there?

112
00:06:08,210 --> 00:06:10,521
Well, I haven't been there yet,

113
00:06:10,545 --> 00:06:12,157
but the big guy told me all about it.

114
00:06:12,181 --> 00:06:14,059
He says he'll take me there one of these days.

115
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:15,277
You must be close.

116
00:06:15,301 --> 00:06:17,746
Ah, save a guy's life once or twice

117
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:20,019
he sort of starts to hang on ya. I don't mind.

118
00:06:21,557 --> 00:06:23,540
♪

119
00:06:30,232 --> 00:06:31,209
Watch it, idiot.

120
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:32,794
Whoa, uh, sorry.

121
00:06:32,818 --> 00:06:34,329
Wait a second.

122
00:06:34,353 --> 00:06:36,247
You're Superman's twerp, ain't ya?

123
00:06:36,271 --> 00:06:39,150
Uh, not exact... This is perfect.

124
00:06:39,174 --> 00:06:42,036
Superman put my best buddy in the slammer.

125
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:46,224
Now I'm gonna put his buddy in the morgue.

126
00:06:46,248 --> 00:06:47,897
♪

127
00:06:53,846 --> 00:06:55,290
So how do you call Superman?

128
00:06:55,314 --> 00:06:57,026
I yell, same as anyone else.

129
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:58,027
Ah!

130
00:06:58,051 --> 00:06:59,461
Run. Get help.

131
00:06:59,485 --> 00:07:01,112
Hey. Hey, come on.

132
00:07:01,136 --> 00:07:02,113
[MEN SHOUTING]

133
00:07:02,137 --> 00:07:03,949
MAN: Get him!

134
00:07:03,973 --> 00:07:06,468
Help, Superman.

135
00:07:06,492 --> 00:07:08,626
Jimmy Olsen needs help.

136
00:07:37,423 --> 00:07:39,223
Huh?

137
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:43,405
[GRUNTS]

138
00:07:43,429 --> 00:07:44,440
Yah!

139
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:46,113
You're kidding, right?

140
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:54,733
MAN: I think we better get outta here.

141
00:07:54,757 --> 00:07:55,784
MAN 2: No trouble.

142
00:07:55,808 --> 00:07:57,942
Let's go! Come on!

143
00:07:59,028 --> 00:08:00,438
You okay?

144
00:08:00,462 --> 00:08:01,623
Jimmy.

145
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,959
Oh, thank God, you're all right.

146
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:05,543
You heard me.

147
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:07,463
You really are friends with Jimmy.

148
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:10,799
He's all right. But you better clear up this "pal" stuff.

149
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:12,790
I can't be within earshot every time.

150
00:08:21,150 --> 00:08:22,645
Whoa. Hey, Angela.

151
00:08:22,669 --> 00:08:24,329
No time, kid.

152
00:08:24,353 --> 00:08:25,902
Wait. Listen.

153
00:08:27,489 --> 00:08:29,418
You gotta take back that story about me.

154
00:08:29,442 --> 00:08:31,320
I almost got killed last night.

155
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:35,896
Take it back? I make him a star, and this is the thanks I get.

156
00:08:43,772 --> 00:08:45,750
You're Superman's friend, right?

157
00:08:45,774 --> 00:08:48,053
No, I swear. It isn't me.

158
00:08:48,077 --> 00:08:50,155
I know Superman. He pulled me out of the drink once

159
00:08:50,179 --> 00:08:51,623
when my boat sank.

160
00:08:51,647 --> 00:08:54,392
Yeah, if it wasn't for Superman, I'd be a goner for sure.

161
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:56,762
Come to think of it, I never got to thank the big lug.

162
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:58,747
Tell you what, if I wrote him a thank-you note,

163
00:08:58,771 --> 00:08:59,765
you think you could...

164
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:01,299
MAN: Pass an invitation on to him?

165
00:09:01,323 --> 00:09:04,269
My kid's birthday's coming up, and he just loves Superman.

166
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:05,821
Superman this, Superman that.

167
00:09:05,845 --> 00:09:07,189
♪

168
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:09,291
If I wasn't such a secure father, I'd be jealous.

169
00:09:09,315 --> 00:09:11,577
Anyway, the little guy'd really appreciate it...

170
00:09:11,601 --> 00:09:12,694
If Big Blue would do

171
00:09:12,718 --> 00:09:14,963
an endorsement on one of our TV spots.

172
00:09:14,987 --> 00:09:16,531
We're Big Blue Automotive.

173
00:09:16,555 --> 00:09:18,784
And don't you worry, you'd get a finder's fee.

174
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:20,769
I take care of my friends. Frankly, my boy,

175
00:09:20,793 --> 00:09:22,488
you have no idea how much it would mean...

176
00:09:22,512 --> 00:09:23,705
To all the little baby seals

177
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:26,125
if Superman would come to our charity dinner.

178
00:09:26,149 --> 00:09:29,645
It's black-tie, but he could come as-is, of course.

179
00:09:29,669 --> 00:09:31,964
So do you think you could show him these pamphlets?

180
00:09:31,988 --> 00:09:33,631
It wouldn't take him long to read them.

181
00:09:33,655 --> 00:09:34,967
I mean, he is Superman, right?

182
00:09:34,991 --> 00:09:36,601
[GRUNTS]

183
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:39,304
And it would really help raise awareness of the hardship...

184
00:09:39,328 --> 00:09:41,372
MAN: I have to put up with because of that noisy,

185
00:09:41,396 --> 00:09:45,243
stinking neighbor of mine. Now, if Superman was to pop by

186
00:09:45,267 --> 00:09:48,364
and lay a few of those super punches into the wall,

187
00:09:48,388 --> 00:09:51,622
then that louse would turn down his stereo.

188
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:55,537
Hey, I ain't done talkin' to you's yet!

189
00:09:55,561 --> 00:09:59,041
GIRL: Oh, look, it's Superman's friend.

190
00:09:59,065 --> 00:10:00,292
[ALL SQUEALING]

191
00:10:00,316 --> 00:10:02,111
GIRL 2: He's even cuter than his picture.

192
00:10:02,135 --> 00:10:03,462
GIRL 3: Oh, come here.

193
00:10:03,486 --> 00:10:04,880
Oh, you could be my baby.

194
00:10:04,904 --> 00:10:06,114
[SQUEALING]

195
00:10:06,138 --> 00:10:07,866
GIRL: Come back. Come back.

196
00:10:07,890 --> 00:10:10,135
He's mine, mine.

197
00:10:10,159 --> 00:10:13,922
GIRL 3: I want him for me, for me and my sister.

198
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,390
He's just what we're looking for.

199
00:10:15,414 --> 00:10:16,424
GIRL 4: He's so cute.

200
00:10:16,448 --> 00:10:18,816
GIRL 3: Oh, God.

201
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:22,264
[SCREECHING TIRES]

202
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:23,565
Jimmy, get in.

203
00:10:23,589 --> 00:10:26,350
GIRL: I almost got him, I almost got him.

204
00:10:27,794 --> 00:10:29,438
[ALL WHINING]

205
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:32,024
I have got to get Angela to take back that story.

206
00:10:32,048 --> 00:10:34,943
Why would she do that? It's true, isn't it?

207
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,278
No.

208
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:37,545
But...

209
00:10:37,569 --> 00:10:39,714
you're special to Superman. I saw it myself.

210
00:10:39,738 --> 00:10:41,700
He showed up to rescue you and everything.

211
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,968
Yeah, but he'd do that for anyone.

212
00:10:43,992 --> 00:10:45,621
People are making too much of this.

213
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:46,888
I need a break.

214
00:10:46,912 --> 00:10:50,047
Don't worry. I'll take you somewhere private.

215
00:11:06,549 --> 00:11:07,659
Wh-what are we doing here?

216
00:11:07,683 --> 00:11:10,312
I want you to meet a friend of mine.

217
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:11,446
At a scrap yard?

218
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:12,736
You'll see.

219
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:19,893
♪

220
00:11:23,565 --> 00:11:25,227
MAN: What is this?

221
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:28,402
Why have you brought me him?

222
00:11:30,857 --> 00:11:32,155
[GASPS]

223
00:11:47,563 --> 00:11:49,575
Mmm-mwah.

224
00:11:49,599 --> 00:11:51,293
Hi, honey.

225
00:11:51,317 --> 00:11:53,129
What is going on?

226
00:11:53,153 --> 00:11:54,130
Shut up.

227
00:11:54,154 --> 00:11:56,398
I'd like an explanation myself.

228
00:11:56,422 --> 00:11:58,667
You were supposed to bring Lois.

229
00:11:58,691 --> 00:12:00,402
Lane was too hard to trick.

230
00:12:00,426 --> 00:12:01,875
This one was easy.

231
00:12:03,079 --> 00:12:05,975
But will Superman come for him?

232
00:12:05,999 --> 00:12:07,676
Trust me. They're good friends.

233
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:10,412
I even staged a test last night.

234
00:12:10,436 --> 00:12:11,436
Mmm-mwah.

235
00:12:21,731 --> 00:12:22,708
Ah!

236
00:12:22,732 --> 00:12:23,852
[CRASH] Huh?

237
00:12:57,217 --> 00:12:58,365
Ahh!

238
00:13:03,289 --> 00:13:05,606
[MACHINERY RUMBLING]

239
00:13:09,312 --> 00:13:10,761
[GASPS]

240
00:13:26,663 --> 00:13:28,190
Careful.

241
00:13:28,214 --> 00:13:31,310
We don't want to damage our collateral just yet.

242
00:13:31,334 --> 00:13:32,477
Speak for yourself.

243
00:13:32,501 --> 00:13:34,480
You didn't have to spend an evening with him.

244
00:13:34,504 --> 00:13:36,903
[SCREAMS]

245
00:13:38,975 --> 00:13:40,619
[WHIMPERING]

246
00:13:40,643 --> 00:13:42,854
And I thought I was cold-hearted.

247
00:13:42,878 --> 00:13:45,679
I learned from the best, sweetie.

248
00:13:47,083 --> 00:13:48,961
[PHONE RINGS] Lane.

249
00:13:48,985 --> 00:13:51,714
<i>Lois? It's Tina.</i>

250
00:13:51,738 --> 00:13:53,938
Jimmy and I have been kidnapped.

251
00:14:07,804 --> 00:14:08,847
Sounds like some wacko

252
00:14:08,871 --> 00:14:10,571
wants his manifesto in the paper.

253
00:14:13,426 --> 00:14:14,520
The police traced the call

254
00:14:14,544 --> 00:14:16,071
to a scrap yard north of the city.

255
00:14:16,095 --> 00:14:17,656
They said we should play along

256
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:19,362
until they can scramble a team up there.

257
00:14:22,468 --> 00:14:24,580
I gotta start wearing pants.

258
00:14:24,604 --> 00:14:26,920
♪

259
00:14:39,952 --> 00:14:41,964
JIMMY: Superman.

260
00:14:41,988 --> 00:14:44,588
Superman, it's a trap. It's...

261
00:14:46,459 --> 00:14:47,858
Metallo.

262
00:14:49,913 --> 00:14:51,862
[GRUNTING]

263
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:03,819
Ah!

264
00:15:03,843 --> 00:15:06,588
Looks like I've caught you off-guard, Superman.

265
00:15:06,612 --> 00:15:09,513
You've come without your protective outerwear.

266
00:15:18,908 --> 00:15:21,303
[BLOWS THUDDING]

267
00:15:21,327 --> 00:15:23,138
[GRUNTS]

268
00:15:23,162 --> 00:15:25,808
It's remarkable how easy this is

269
00:15:25,832 --> 00:15:29,678
once I have you alone and unprepared.

270
00:15:29,702 --> 00:15:31,764
If it wasn't so much fun,

271
00:15:31,788 --> 00:15:33,754
I might actually feel bad for you.

272
00:15:38,795 --> 00:15:39,855
Brought me a present?

273
00:15:39,879 --> 00:15:42,691
Call this off. Stop him.

274
00:15:42,715 --> 00:15:44,360
Me stop him?

275
00:15:44,384 --> 00:15:46,946
You've got a twisted sense of who's working for whom.

276
00:15:46,970 --> 00:15:49,448
How could you help him? He's killing Superman.

277
00:15:49,472 --> 00:15:50,699
What can I say?

278
00:15:50,723 --> 00:15:51,933
Hyah!

279
00:15:51,957 --> 00:15:53,173
Ah!

280
00:15:54,611 --> 00:15:56,354
I'm into metal. Ha!

281
00:15:56,378 --> 00:15:57,995
Ooh!

282
00:16:00,049 --> 00:16:02,878
Hee... Ha!

283
00:16:02,902 --> 00:16:04,368
Ugh. Oh.

284
00:16:05,071 --> 00:16:07,054
Ow!

285
00:16:07,473 --> 00:16:08,884
Hey.

286
00:16:08,908 --> 00:16:11,870
Let me out, you little runt.

287
00:16:11,894 --> 00:16:13,360
Let me out!

288
00:16:15,048 --> 00:16:17,247
Oh!

289
00:16:19,636 --> 00:16:21,563
[CRASH]

290
00:16:21,587 --> 00:16:22,602
What?

291
00:16:30,229 --> 00:16:32,929
[GRUNTING]

292
00:16:40,823 --> 00:16:43,441
[GROANING]

293
00:16:47,964 --> 00:16:48,964
Ah!

294
00:16:54,787 --> 00:16:55,787
Ugh.

295
00:16:59,558 --> 00:17:00,991
Care to try again?

296
00:17:08,650 --> 00:17:10,362
Come, now, Superman.

297
00:17:10,386 --> 00:17:13,754
Do you really think you'll ever win this way?

298
00:17:14,474 --> 00:17:16,340
[GRUNTING]

299
00:17:18,728 --> 00:17:20,660
Ahh!

300
00:17:22,398 --> 00:17:23,530
[GROWLING]

301
00:17:34,143 --> 00:17:35,143
Ah!

302
00:17:51,544 --> 00:17:53,326
[METAL RUMBLING]

303
00:17:56,682 --> 00:17:59,328
[LAUGHING]

304
00:17:59,352 --> 00:18:03,332
I must say, you two make quite a team.

305
00:18:03,356 --> 00:18:06,668
Dramatic, but feeble.

306
00:18:06,692 --> 00:18:10,677
[GRUNTING]

307
00:18:22,692 --> 00:18:25,320
What was that supposed to be?

308
00:18:25,344 --> 00:18:27,573
Battery acid.

309
00:18:27,597 --> 00:18:29,613
[SIZZLING]

310
00:18:33,936 --> 00:18:34,936
Ah!

311
00:19:00,896 --> 00:19:02,679
SUPERMAN: Still kicking yourself?

312
00:19:03,849 --> 00:19:05,249
Why shouldn't I?

313
00:19:06,318 --> 00:19:09,597
I messed things up bigtime.

314
00:19:09,621 --> 00:19:11,399
You lived up to your press, Jimmy.

315
00:19:11,423 --> 00:19:13,885
You saved my life again.

316
00:19:13,909 --> 00:19:17,072
Here, I made you a thank-you gift.

317
00:19:17,096 --> 00:19:19,140
You didn't have to.

318
00:19:19,164 --> 00:19:21,410
I mean, you've saved my life too.

319
00:19:21,434 --> 00:19:24,029
Only like a million times.

320
00:19:24,053 --> 00:19:25,581
It's not just a watch.

321
00:19:25,605 --> 00:19:28,750
This button emits a hypersonic signal.

322
00:19:28,774 --> 00:19:32,187
If I'm anywhere in the city, I'll hear it and I'll come.

323
00:19:32,211 --> 00:19:33,721
I figured you might need it

324
00:19:33,745 --> 00:19:36,057
now that everyone knows we're friends.

325
00:19:36,081 --> 00:19:37,914
Just don't wear it out.

326
00:19:53,791 --> 00:19:56,642
♪

